body:
Verilator: `Verilator 5.007 devel rev v5.006-7-g4a8cfe367`
OS: Ubuntu 20.04 / WSL2 on Windows 10

---

Attempting to get a handle for an object with a very long name via `vpi_handle_by_name()` fails, because the hashed name is used for comparison.

Example:
```SystemVerilog
// Copyright cocotb contributors
// Licensed under the Revised BSD License, see LICENSE for details.
// SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause

`timescale 1us/1us

module test (
    input logic ,
    output logic o);

assign o = ;

endmodule
```

VPI trace in debug mode:

```
-V{t1,15}- vpi: vpi_handle_by_name test. (nil)
```

Snippet of generated code with hashed name:
```cpp
// This class is the main interface to the Verilated model
class Vtop VL_NOT_FINAL : public VerilatedModel {
  private:
    // Symbol table holding complete model state (owned by this class)
    Vtop__Syms* const vlSymsp;

  public:

    // PORTS
    // The application code writes and reads these signals to
    // propagate new values into/out from the Verilated model.
    VL_IN8(&KPFIVTM1LHY0OFUNXF0XZO1RV535NNU4__VhshD3eKqDQiWsld0TP5Y2piclkYJARKk5NIBBH5Tmog,0,0);
    VL_OUT8(&o,0,0);
```
